DML- SELECT QUERY 2 (GROUP BY, AGGREGATE FUNCTIONS)


1. List product name, price except soap on price order.

mysql> select *from product;
+-----+--------------+---------+
| pid | pname        | price   |
+-----+--------------+---------+
|  54 | soap         |   35.00 |
| 404 | milk         |   25.50 |
| 408 | pringles     |  102.00 |
| 409 | sauce        |   71.40 |
| 411 | nonstick pan |  714.00 |
| 414 | maggi        |  153.00 |
| 423 | cooker       | 1734.00 |
| 448 | pen          |   10.20 |
+-----+--------------+---------+
8 rows in set (0.00 sec)


mysql> select pname,price from product where pname!='soap' order by price;;
+--------------+---------+
| pname        | price   |
+--------------+---------+
| pen          |   10.20 |
| milk         |   25.50 |
| sauce        |   71.40 |
| pringles     |  102.00 |
| maggi        |  153.00 |
| nonstick pan |  714.00 |
| cooker       | 1734.00 |
+--------------+---------+
7 rows in set (0.00 sec)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


2. Find minimum, maximum and average price of products.

mysql> select *from product;
+-----+--------------+---------+
| pid | pname        | price   |
+-----+--------------+---------+
|  54 | soap         |   35.00 |
| 404 | milk         |   25.50 |
| 408 | pringles     |  102.00 |
| 409 | sauce        |   71.40 |
| 411 | nonstick pan |  714.00 |
| 414 | maggi        |  153.00 |
| 423 | cooker       | 1734.00 |
| 448 | pen          |   10.20 |
+-----+--------------+---------+
8 rows in set (0.00 sec)




mysql> select min(price),max(price), avg(price) as average_price from product;
+------------+------------+---------------+
| min(price) | max(price) | average_price |
+------------+------------+---------------+
|      10.20 |    1734.00 |    355.637500 |
+------------+------------+---------------+
1 row in set (0.01 sec)


